# <type>: <YL-number> (Just copy the key of the Jira ticket) <subject> (Max 50 char)

# Remember blank line between title and body.

# Body: Explain WHAT and WHY (not HOW). Include Github issue
# Example: Github issue #14
# (Max 72 char)
# - WHAT
# - WHY

# ---COMMIT END---
# Type can be
#    feat        (new feature)
#    fix         (bug fix)
#    refactor    (refactoring production code)
#    style       (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#    docs        (changes to documentation)
#    test        (adding or refactoring tests; no production code change)
#    chore       (updating grunt tasks etc; no production code change)
#    revert      (annulation of a commit)
#    perf        (improvement of performance in code)
#    build       (compilation or bundling)
#    ci          (continuous integration)
#    cd          (continuous delivery)
#    gitWorkflow (collaboration)
